Structs/Behavior.html#/s:21PersonalityIn.name: traitID
Structs/Behavior.html#/s:21PersonalityIn.abstract: The unique identifier of the characteristic to which the results pertain. IDs have the form behavior_{value}.

Structs/Behavior.html#/s:21PersonalityIn.name: category
Structs/Behavior.html#/s:21PersonalityIn.abstract: The category of the characteristic: behavior for temporal data.

Structs/Behavior.html#/s:21PersonalityIn.name: percentage
Structs/Behavior.html#/s:21PersonalityIn.abstract: For JSON content that is timestamped, the percentage of timestamped input data that occurred during that day of the week or hour of the day. The range is 0 to 1.

Structs/Content.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: contentItems
Structs/Content.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: An array of ContentItem objects that provides the text that is to be analyzed.

Structs/ConsumptionPreferencesCategory.h.name: consumptionPreferenceCategoryID
Structs/ConsumptionPreferencesCategory.h.abstract: The unique identifier of the consumption preferences category to which the results pertain. IDs have the form consumption_preferences_{category}.

Structs/ConsumptionPreferencesCategory.h.name: name
Structs/ConsumptionPreferencesCategory.h.abstract: The user-visible name of the consumption preferences category.

Structs/ConsumptionPreferencesCategory.h.name: consumptionPreferences
Structs/ConsumptionPreferencesCategory.h.abstract: Detailed results inferred from the input text for the individual preferences of the category.

Structs/ConsumptionPreferences.html#/s:2.name: consumptionPreferenceID
Structs/ConsumptionPreferences.html#/s:2.abstract: The unique identifier of the consumption preference to which the results pertain. IDs have the form consumption_preferences_{preference}.

Structs/ConsumptionPreferences.html#/s:2.name: name
Structs/ConsumptionPreferences.html#/s:2.abstract: The user-visible name of the consumption preference.

Structs/ConsumptionPreferences.html#/s:2.name: score
Structs/ConsumptionPreferences.html#/s:2.abstract: The score for the consumption preference: * 0.0: Unlikely * 0.5: Neutral * 1.0: Likely The scores for some preferences are binary and do not allow a neutral value. The score is an indication of preference based on the results inferred from the input text, not a normalized percentile.

Structs/ContentItem/Contenttype.html.name: Contenttype
Structs/ContentItem/Contenttype.html.abstract: MIME type of the content. The default is plain text. The tags are stripped from HTML content before it is analyzed; plain text is processed as submitted.

Structs/ContentItem/Language.html.name: Language
Structs/ContentItem/Language.html.abstract: Language identifier (two-letter ISO 639-1 identifier) for the language of the content item. The default is en (English). Regional variants are treated as their parent language; for example, en-US is interpreted as en. A language specified with the Content-Type header overrides the value of this parameter; any content items that specify a different language are ignored. Omit the Content-Type header to base the language on the most prevalent specification among the content items; again, content items that specify a different language are ignored. You can specify any combination of languages for the input and response content.

Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.name: content
Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.abstract: Content that is to be analyzed. The service supports up to 20 MB of content for all items combined.

Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.name: created
Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.abstract: Timestamp that identifies when this content was created. Specify a value in milliseconds since the UNIX Epoch (January 1, 1970, at 0:00 UTC). Required only for results that include temporal behavior data.

Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.name: updated
Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.abstract: Timestamp that identifies when this content was last updated. Specify a value in milliseconds since the UNIX Epoch (January 1, 1970, at 0:00 UTC). Required only for results that include temporal behavior data.

Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.name: contenttype
Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.abstract: MIME type of the content. The default is plain text. The tags are stripped from HTML content before it is analyzed; plain text is processed as submitted.

Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.name: language
Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.abstract: Language identifier (two-letter ISO 639-1 identifier) for the language of the content item. The default is en (English). Regional variants are treated as their parent language; for example, en-US is interpreted as en. A language specified with the Content-Type header overrides the value of this parameter; any content items that specify a different language are ignored. Omit the Content-Type header to base the language on the most prevalent specification among the content items; again, content items that specify a different language are ignored. You can specify any combination of languages for the input and response content.

Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.name: parentid
Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.abstract: Unique ID of the parent content item for this item. Used to identify hierarchical relationships between posts/replies, messages/replies, and so on.

Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.name: reply
Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.abstract: Indicates whether this content item is a reply to another content item.

Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.name: forward
Structs/ContentItem.html#/s:21Personalit.abstract: Indicates whether this content item is a forwarded/copied version of another content item.

Structs/Trait/Category.html.name: Category
Structs/Trait/Category.html.abstract: The category of the characteristic: * personality for Big Five personality characteristics * needs for Needs * values for Values.

Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.name: traitID
Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.abstract: The unique identifier of the characteristic to which the results pertain. IDs have the form big5_{characteristic} for Big Five personality characteristics, need_{characteristic} for Needs, or value_{characteristic} for Values.

Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.name: category
Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.abstract: The category of the characteristic: * personality for Big Five personality characteristics * needs for Needs * values for Values.

Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.name: percentile
Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.abstract: The normalized percentile score for the characteristic. The range is 0 to 1. For example, if the percentage for Openness is 0.60, the author scored in the 60th percentile; the author is more open than 59 percent of the population and less open than 39 percent of the population.

Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.name: rawScore
Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.abstract: The raw score for the characteristic. The range is 0 to 1. A higher score generally indicates a greater likelihood that the author has that characteristic, but raw scores must be considered in aggregate: The range of values in practice might be much smaller than 0 to 1, so an individual score must be considered in the context of the overall scores and their range. The raw score is computed based on the input and the service model; it is not normalized or compared with a sample population. The raw score enables comparison of the results against a different sampling population and with a custom normalization approach.

Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.name: significant
Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.abstract: 2017-10-13: Indicates whether the characteristic is meaningful for the input language. The field is always true for all characteristics of English, Spanish, and Japanese input. The field is false for the subset of characteristics of Arabic and Korean input for which the service’s models are unable to generate meaningful results. **2016-10-19: Not returned.

Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.name: children
Structs/Trait.html#/s:21PersonalityInsig.abstract: For personality (Big Five) dimensions, more detailed results for the facets of each dimension as inferred from the input text.

Structs/Profile/ProcessedLanguage.html.name: ProcessedLanguage
Structs/Profile/ProcessedLanguage.html.abstract: The language model that was used to process the input.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: processedLanguage
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: The language model that was used to process the input.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: wordCount
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: The number of words that were found in the input.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: wordCountMessage
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: When guidance is appropriate, a string that provides a message that indicates the number of words found and where that value falls in the range of required or suggested number of words.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: personality
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: Detailed results for the Big Five personality characteristics (dimensions and facets) inferred from the input text.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: values
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: Detailed results for the Needs characteristics inferred from the input text.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: needs
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: Detailed results for the Values characteristics inferred from the input text.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: behavior
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: For JSON content that is timestamped, detailed results about the social behavior disclosed by the input in terms of temporal characteristics. The results include information about the distribution of the content over the days of the week and the hours of the day.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: consumptionPreferences
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: If the consumption_preferences query parameter is true, detailed results for each category of consumption preferences. Each element of the array provides information inferred from the input text for the individual preferences of that category.

Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: warnings
Structs/Profile.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: Warning messages associated with the input text submitted with the request. The array is empty if the input generated no warnings.

Structs/Warning.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.name: message
Structs/Warning.html#/s:21PersonalityIns.abstract: The message associated with the warning_id: * WORD_COUNT_MESSAGE: There were {number} words in the input. We need a minimum of 600, preferably 1,200 or more, to compute statistically significant estimates. * JSON_AS_TEXT: Request input was processed as text/plain as indicated, however detected a JSON input. Did you mean application/json? * CONTENT_TRUNCATED: For maximum accuracy while also optimizing processing time, only the first 250KB of input text (excluding markup) was analyzed. Accuracy levels off at approximately 3,000 words so this did not affect the accuracy of the profile. * PARTIAL_TEXT_USED, The text provided to compute the profile was trimmed for performance reasons. This action does not affect the accuracy of the output, as not all of the input text was required. Applies only when Arabic input text exceeds a threshold at which additional words do not contribute to the accuracy of the profile.

Structs.html#/s:21PersonalityInsightsV31.name: JSONWrapper
Structs.html#/s:21PersonalityInsightsV31.abstract: Used internally to serialize and deserialize JSON.
